															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/communism-will-win" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(617958); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=617958&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610164245" alt="Communism will win" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=617958)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/communism-will-win" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(617958); return false;" >Communism will win</a></span> <span class="odate time_1362004389 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">27 Feb 2013 22:33</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1720729">
									

<p>Alternative interpretation, building off of this: Experiencing nothingness is simply a facet of SCP-447. There's something after death (and the Foundation knows that because <a href="/scp-1704">they've been there</a>), but in the process of bringing you back, in denying you the ability to experience this afterlife, SCP-447 functionally destroys your soul and deprives a consciousness of any real meaning it could experience.</p>
<p>SCP-447 is bad in the same way that the Total Perspective Vortex is &#8212; plenty of things can kill your body, but SCP-447 kills your <em>soul.</em> And that's why its effect on dead bodies is expunged and experiments are denied &#8212; doing so would be infinitely more unethical than anything as passe as killing lots of people (because that doesn't ultimately matter), to the point where they don't want anyone to know that they've done so.</p>

