				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser deleted" data-id="1313607"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/common--images/avatars/default/a16.png" alt=""/>(account deleted)</span> <span class="odate time_1362193300 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">02 Mar 2013 03:01</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-1722391">
									

<p>I think it's funny that Scantron said that this was personally resonant &quot;as an atheist&quot;, because as not-an-atheist, this is not only reflective of my headcanon of the Foundation but reminiscent of my general state of mind, too. Certain swathes of this monologue outline exactly how I would perceive the Foundation if it were <em>real</em> and really went about its business the way we present it.</p>
<p>I guess in that sense&#8230; I don't really find this <em>threatening</em> or even as deep as the well of nihilism goes. But then, &quot;threatening&quot; doesn't seem to be the thrust of the tale, and I appreciate it for taking a nuanced approached to a mystery that mostly invites images of mass grossness and destruction. If nothing else, it's got a nice, consistent tone. +1</p>

							</div>

								
